comments: Sexton (UTA) establishes himself in Winslow's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs as Winslow slides into the pick.
Simons (POR) brings his forearm to Clarkson's (UTA) front and the contact affects Clarkson's SQBR during the drive.

Olynyk (UTA) brings his hands to Watford's (POR) front and extends them out slightly as he releases away during the inbound play. The contact is marginal and Watford's reaction is not commensurate with the degree of contact.
Sexton (UTA) establishes himself in Grant's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs as Grant commits to going under the screen.
Simons (POR) moves along Sexton's (UTA) path and the contact during the drive is marginal.
Simons (POR) reaches in for the the ball and deflects Sexton's (UTA) dribble out of bounds. Possession is correctly retained by Utah.
Watford (POR) extends his forearm to Olynyk's (UTA) side and the offensive player briefly lifts his left arm around Watford's arm. The marginal contact dissolves shortly thereafter.
Clarkson (UTA) jumps slightly forward during his jump shot attempt and Winslow (POR) initiates marginal contact with Clarkson's lower body after the release.
Olynyk (UTA) lifts his arm towards the ball and Watford (POR) is able to maintain control of the rebound through the marginal contact.
Sexton (UTA) and Grant (POR) jostle for position in the post and the contact is marginal.
Nurkic (POR) brings his left arm out behind him and the contact with Markkanen (UTA) is marginal with the entry pass imminent.
Markkanen (UTA) legally contests Nurkic's (POR) shot attempt in the post.
Watford (POR) places his right arm on Olynyk's (UTA) side during the post backdown and the contact is marginal.
Nurkic (POR) avoids making contact with Olynyk's (UTA) arm and legally contests Olynyk's jump shot attempt.
Grant (POR) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Clarkson's (UTA) path and some contact occurs as the two players come together.
Simons (POR) extends his off-arm into Vanderbilt (UTA), who was moving alongside Simons' path. The contact dislodges Vanderbilt from his legal guarding position.
Nurkic (POR) and Olynyk (UTA) come together at the same spot on the floor and the contact is marginal.
Markkanen (UTA) jumps vertically and absorbs the contact with Simons (POR) during the driving shot attempt. Markkanen then lowers his arm down and cleanly blocks Simons' driving shot attempt.
Grant (POR) has a resting hand to Markkanen's (UTA) side and the contact while Markkanen is in possession of the ball is marginal.

Markkanen (UTA) throws a pass that goes into the backcourt, where it is first touched by Olynyk (UTA). Olynyk makes contact with the ball and the violation is whistled prior to the contact during the loose ball.
Clarkson (UTA) moves laterally into Simons' (POR) path and the ensuing body contact impacts Simons' SQBR.
Olynyk (UTA) does not inbound the ball within five seconds.
Vanderbilt (UTA) establishes himself in Grant's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the screen.
Nurkic (POR) briefly brings his arm toward Markkanen's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs when Markkanen loses control of the ball during his drive.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Markkanen (UTA) is the last player to touch the ball prior to it going out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to Portland.
Watford (POR) brings his hands toward Vanderbilt (UTA) and marginal contact occurs as Watford releases away from the defender.
Clarkson (UTA) initiates contact with Grant's (POR) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Simons (POR) makes contact with the ball and cleanly dislodges it from Clarkson (UTA) during his upward shooting motion.
Clarkson (UTA) extends his leg and he kicks the ball.
Vanderbilt (UTA) reaches in to deflect the pass and marginal contact occurs with Grant's (POR) arm that he is able to play on through.
Clarkson (UTA) commits a take foul on Grant (POR). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
